===[[Etymology]]===

French from Latin ''[[fractio]]'', '''breaking''', from ''[[frangere]]'', '''break'''

# a part of a whole
# (''Mathematics'') a [[rational number]] written as two [[integer]]s, one over the other and separated by a horizontal bar, or side by side and separated by a [[slash]]; or in [[decimal notation]] using a [[decimal point]].
# a tiny part-"a fraction of the cost"
# part of a particular society or group.

